1:20:21.708 --> 1:20:27.500
I have flown to Beirut twice
in my husband's space machine.

1:20:27.667 --> 1:20:33.042
And the witch doctor of Atlas.
Alexis, stop me from flying away.

1:20:33.208 --> 1:20:37.375
The boat is pitching,
and you know how light I am.

1:20:45.333 --> 1:20:47.958
Ferdinand, help me.

1:20:58.083 --> 1:21:01.708
- Ferdinand, we weigh anchor in an hour.
- Yes, Princess.

1:21:01.875 --> 1:21:05.208
Alexis, we're going into town.

1:21:09.417 --> 1:21:10.792
Pierrot!

1:21:28.000 --> 1:21:31.625
- It's me.
- My name is Ferdinand.

1:21:31.792 --> 1:21:33.250
Hi.

1:21:33.417 --> 1:21:36.792
You don't look surprised to see me.

1:21:36.917 --> 1:21:41.333
- What are you doing here?
- I'm happy.

1:21:41.500 --> 1:21:44.417
I've finally found you.

1:21:45.500 --> 1:21:48.708
- Where do you live now?
- With you, you fool.

1:21:48.875 --> 1:21:53.667
I'll be living with you.
I've been looking for you everywhere.

1:21:57.542 --> 1:22:02.500
- Why didn't you wait for me?
- I wanted to.

1:22:02.667 --> 1:22:05.917
I managed to get away before they arrived.

1:22:06.083 --> 1:22:09.792
I ran to the nightclub
to warn you not to come over,

1:22:09.958 --> 1:22:12.208
but I didn't find you.

1:22:12.333 --> 1:22:18.125
So I went back and saw those men
getting into the blue Ford.

1:22:18.292 --> 1:22:21.208
I thought they'd killed you.

1:22:22.458 --> 1:22:28.083
So I went away. I don't even know where I went.

1:22:28.250 --> 1:22:31.750
But I was afraid of going back to the seaside.

1:22:31.917 --> 1:22:37.542
And then one day, I ran into Fred,
in Toulon, in a bar,

1:22:37.708 --> 1:22:41.125
the Las Vegas bar, in Toulon.

1:22:41.292 --> 1:22:45.625
- How did you find out I was here?
- By accident.

1:22:45.792 --> 1:22:48.375
It's true, you know.

1:22:50.208 --> 1:22:52.375
I believe you, you liar.

1:22:52.542 --> 1:22:57.625
Why won't you ever believe I love you?
I love you in my own way.

1:22:57.792 --> 1:22:59.875
Yes, that's true.

1:23:00.042 --> 1:23:01.458
I'll prove it.

1:23:01.625 --> 1:23:06.167
Look. Yesterday, I went to our beach
and picked up your journal.

1:23:06.333 --> 1:23:08.042
Thank you.

1:23:08.208 --> 1:23:11.458
Look at the last page.

1:23:11.625 --> 1:23:15.333
I wrote a little poem about you.

1:23:15.500 --> 1:23:18.542
"Tender and cruel,

1:23:18.708 --> 1:23:22.125
real and surreal,

1:23:22.333 --> 1:23:25.333
terrifying and funny,

1:23:25.500 --> 1:23:28.583
nocturnal and diurnal,

1:23:28.750 --> 1:23:33.583
usual and unusual, as handsome as anything..."

1:23:33.750 --> 1:23:36.542
- Pierrot is mad!
- My name is Ferdinand.

1:23:36.708 --> 1:23:42.042
- Stop bugging me, damn it!
- If you think saying that suits you...

1:23:42.208 --> 1:23:46.542
- God, too, can go to...
- Don't talk like that.

1:23:46.708 --> 1:23:51.042
Listen to her! We're wanted for murder.
Do you know what that is?

1:23:51.208 --> 1:23:55.375
Of course I do. So what? Does it scare you?

1:23:56.417 --> 1:23:58.083
Answer me.

1:23:58.250 --> 1:24:02.292
I look at you, I listen to you,
but that's not what matters.

1:24:02.458 --> 1:24:05.792
- Thanks.
- No, I mean, at this very moment.

1:24:05.958 --> 1:24:07.958
Well, it has already passed.

1:24:08.125 --> 1:24:13.792
Our relationship
is a bit like the blue of the sky.

1:24:13.958 --> 1:24:16.917
I don't understand.

1:24:17.083 --> 1:24:19.875
I'd like time to stand still.

1:24:20.042 --> 1:24:26.083
When I put my hand on your knee,
that, in itself, is wonderful.

1:24:26.250 --> 1:24:30.875
That's what life is about: space, feelings.

1:24:32.750 --> 1:24:37.042
Instead, I'm going to follow you back
to our tale of sound and fury.

1:24:37.208 --> 1:24:40.500
- Actually, I don't care.
- Come on, Fred's waiting for us.

1:24:40.667 --> 1:24:43.583
All right, never mind. Let's go.

1:24:47.000 --> 1:24:50.542
What are the police up to?
We should have been in jail long ago.

1:24:50.667 --> 1:24:54.833
They're clever.
They let people destroy themselves.

1:25:23.292 --> 1:25:29.375
- Why do you do things like that?
- I keep telling you I didn't kill him.

1:25:45.333 --> 1:25:47.958
It's funny to be alive, when so many have died.

1:25:48.167 --> 1:25:49.792
Oh, yes, it's funny.

1:25:49.958 --> 1:25:53.875
- This is like the set of <i>Pépé le Moko.</i>
- Who?

1:25:54.042 --> 1:25:56.292
- <i>Pépe' le Moko.</i>
- Who is he?

1:25:56.458 --> 1:25:59.583
You really don't know anything.

1:26:04.500 --> 1:26:09.000
- Do you know what you are?
- A sexual man.

1:26:10.292 --> 1:26:16.458
As if. I know who you are, but you don't.

1:26:16.625 --> 1:26:22.958
It's true. I'm just a big question mark
overlooking the Mediterranean.

1:26:39.792 --> 1:26:44.875
- Are your parents still alive?
- Yes, and they've never been separated.

1:26:45.042 --> 1:26:48.250
They were almost parted, once.

1:26:48.375 --> 1:26:54.083
Dad was going on a trip,
I don't know where. A small trip.

1:26:54.250 --> 1:26:57.833
They didn't have enough money for two tickets.

1:26:58.000 --> 1:27:01.125
Mum accompanied him to the bus.

1:27:01.292 --> 1:27:07.625
And then they looked at each other:
she was below, he was at the window.

1:27:07.792 --> 1:27:11.958
And just as the bus started, dad quickly got off.

1:27:12.125 --> 1:27:14.375
He didn't want to leave my mother.

1:27:14.542 --> 1:27:19.625
And while he was getting off, she was
getting on through the other door.

1:27:19.792 --> 1:27:24.833
She didn't want to leave my father.
In the end, he didn't go on the trip.

1:27:25.042 --> 1:27:27.833
What did you do when you worked in that lift?

1:27:27.958 --> 1:27:31.792
Nothing much. I looked at people's faces.

1:27:31.958 --> 1:27:36.583
- Where was that?
- At the Galeries Lafayette.

1:27:36.750 --> 1:27:40.958
- Why so many questions?
- I'm trying to figure you out.

1:27:41.125 --> 1:27:44.458
I never could, even five years ago.

1:27:44.625 --> 1:27:47.875
I'm a very sentimental person, that's all.

1:27:48.042 --> 1:27:51.292
One has to be pretty stupid
to find that mysterious.

1:27:51.458 --> 1:27:57.500
What does your brother do, exactly?
I never know if you're making stuff up.

1:27:57.667 --> 1:28:02.333
- Oh, my brother...
- What was he doing in Tel Aviv?

1:28:04.542 --> 1:28:07.750
At the moment, there's a war going on in Yemen.

1:28:07.917 --> 1:28:10.875
You really don't know anything.

1:28:11.042 --> 1:28:14.167
He gets money from the royalist government.

1:28:14.333 --> 1:28:17.583
Do the others work for the Arab League?

1:28:17.750 --> 1:28:22.417
- I don't know. Probably.
- Is there really a dancing troupe?

1:28:22.583 --> 1:28:24.208
What's it to you?

1:28:24.375 --> 1:28:29.667
Why does he need a front?
Arms dealing is almost legal these days.

1:28:29.833 --> 1:28:32.542
- What's it to you?
- Just answer.

1:28:32.708 --> 1:28:35.333
I'll tell you something.

1:28:35.500 --> 1:28:40.208
There are 3,600 seconds in an hour.

1:28:41.250 --> 1:28:46.167
That's about 100,000 seconds per day.

1:28:46.333 --> 1:28:49.583
In an average lifetime, that makes...

1:28:51.083 --> 1:28:54.417
250 billion seconds.

1:28:55.708 --> 1:29:00.667
Since we've known each other,
we've spent a month together.

1:29:01.708 --> 1:29:07.458
If we add it all together, I've only
been with you for a few million seconds

1:29:07.625 --> 1:29:11.708
out of the 250 billion
that go to make up your life.

1:29:11.875 --> 1:29:13.333
It's not much.

1:29:13.500 --> 1:29:18.333
So it's hardly surprising
I barely know who he is either.

1:29:41.208 --> 1:29:44.875
- Is he willing to do it?
- He'll do anything I want.

1:29:45.042 --> 1:29:47.625
Oh, what a mess!

1:29:47.792 --> 1:29:50.792
- You know...
- Six, seven, eight.

1:29:50.958 --> 1:29:54.833
- You're doing well!
- One, two, three, four, five...

1:30:13.292 --> 1:30:15.125
- Hi.
